The paper focuses on developing a novel post-hoc visual explanation method for convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the evaluation of the generated saliency maps, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the robustness of the proposed method under adversarial attack, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE).
